<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA5FF91FF0BFAC7FCC5FADC" blockId="11.[136,886,1316,1343]" box="[136,886,1316,1343]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<heading id="BF43A43AFFA5FF91FF0BFAC7FCC5FADC" box="[136,886,1316,1343]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FF0BFAC7FD08FADD" authority="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S.M. Boo" authorityName="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S. M. Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,699,1316,1343]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="ulixei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FF0BFAC7FEE3FADD" bold="true" box="[136,336,1316,1343]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Sargassum ulixei</emphasis>
G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S.M. Boo
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FD44FAC6FCAFFADC" box="[711,796,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDF3723FFFA5FF91FD44FAC6FCAFFADC" box="[711,796,1317,1342]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="7C8F0FD3FFA5FF91FCA9FAC7FCDDFADC" box="[810,878,1316,1342]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1511,1533]" captionTargetBox="[363,1229,201,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[357,1229,190,1487]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Morphology of Sargassum ulixei sp. nov. A. Habit. B, C. Section of axial cells (a) and medullar cells (m). D. Holdfast. E. Sessile blades (arrow head), vesicles (arrow), and receptacles growing above the branch. F–H. Receptacles, zygote (z)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5150062" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5150062/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA5FF91FF0BFA8AFAEAF9ED" blockId="11.[136,1452,1385,1623]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
Thalli with a disc, crustose or conical holdfast. Stipe cylindrical and smooth, blades lanceolate to elliptic, sessile, 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA5FF91FB55FA8AFA95FA9C" box="[1238,1318,1385,1407]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 mm</quantity>
in length and 1.0– 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA5FF91FF64FA6EFE82FA40" box="[231,305,1421,1443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
wide. Nerve expanded, ecostate or faint, with smooth margins. Cryptostomata present. Vesicles elliptical, with smooth margins, sessile, 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA5FF91FEE5FA52FE0BFA24" box="[358,440,1457,1479]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 mm</quantity>
in length. The apical part of the vesicle has a short apicula. Receptacles cylindrical to elliptical, with smooth margins&gt; 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA5FF91FEE9FA36FE2CFA08" box="[362,415,1493,1515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
in length, growing in bunches with blades. Thalli up to 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA5FF91FC31FA36FC5FFA08" box="[946,1004,1493,1514]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
in length, with terete axes and smooth primary axes arising from the stipe, giving rise to numerous secondary branches. Secondary branches 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA5FF91FBBCFA1AFBDDF9EC" box="[1087,1134,1529,1551]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
in length in some thalli.
</paragraph>
