<subSubSection id="ACAE40DDFFA5FF91FF0BF99DFCDEF8E0" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA5FF91FF0BF99DFC21F95E" blockId="11.[136,1452,1662,2076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FF0BF99DFE9DF97A" bold="true" box="[136,302,1662,1688]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The species epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FD99F99DFDEBF97A" authorityName="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S. M. Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[538,600,1662,1688]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="ulixei">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FD99F99DFDEBF97A" box="[538,600,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">ulixei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ refers to the character in Homer’s Odyssey, giving credit to the long trips and difficulties encountered when studying the 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FD18F941FCA6F95E" authorityName="Andrade-Sorcia &amp; Riosmena-Rodríguez &amp; Muñiz-Salazar &amp; López-Vivas &amp; Boo &amp; Lee &amp; Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[667,789,1698,1724]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FD18F941FCA6F95E" box="[667,789,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">Sargassum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxonomy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA5FF91FF3EF927FC3CF93D" blockId="11.[136,1452,1662,2076]" box="[189,911,1732,1759]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
