<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FC63F8E8FBC3F8C7" authorityName="Setchell &amp; Gardner" authorityYear="1924" box="[992,1136,1803,1829]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="johnstonii">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FC63F8E8FC5DF8C7" box="[992,1006,1803,1829]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FB83F8E8FBC3F8C7" box="[1024,1136,1803,1829]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">johnstonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the field. After detailed morphological assessment we found that these specimens shared some characteristics with both 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FB56F8CDFAC9F8AA" authorityName="Setchell &amp; Gardner" authorityYear="1924" box="[1237,1402,1838,1864]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="lapazeanum">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FB56F8CDFB50F8AA" box="[1237,1251,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FB70F8CDFAC9F8AA" box="[1267,1402,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">lapazeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FF0BF8B1FEA6F889" authorityName="Setchell &amp; Gardner" authorityYear="1924" box="[136,277,1873,1900]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="johnstonii">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FF0BF8B1FF25F88E" box="[136,150,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FF26F8B2FEA6F889" box="[165,277,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">johnstonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that these specimens belong to the same section; also there are some similar morphologies. In 
<collectingCountry id="9CA353C6FFA5FF91FF2BF896FEA5F86C" box="[168,278,1908,1935]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">East Asia</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="80256EA7FFA5FF91FEA0F896FE74F86C" author="Kuntze, O." box="[291,455,1908,1935]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="191 - 239" refId="ref13687" refString="Kuntze, O. (1880) Revision von Sargassum und das sogennante Sargasso-Meer. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 1: 191 - 239." type="journal article" year="1880">Kuntze (1880)</bibRefCitation>
reported some specimens similar to 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FCEFF896FEB6F850" authority="(Mertens ex Roth 1800: 104) Kuntze (1880: 215" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1880" baseAuthorityName="Mertens ex Roth" baseAuthorityPageNumber="104" baseAuthorityYear="1800" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="thunbergii">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FCEFF896FCC9F86D" box="[876,890,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FC0AF897FC4EF86C" box="[905,1021,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">thunbergii</emphasis>
(Mertens ex Roth 1800: 104) 
<bibRefCitation id="80256EA7FFA5FF91FAD9F896FEB6F850" author="Kuntze, O." pageId="11" pageNumber="212" pagination="191 - 239" refId="ref13687" refString="Kuntze, O. (1880) Revision von Sargassum und das sogennante Sargasso-Meer. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 1: 191 - 239." type="journal article" year="1880">Kuntze (1880: 215</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 228); however, specimens from the Gulf of California were different and none of the characteristics could be applied to characterize the 
<specimenCount id="F2B2D8DFFFA5FF91FE59F858FDC0F837" box="[474,627,1979,2006]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" type="generic">25 specimens</specimenCount>
collected prior to molecular analysis. Both molecular and morphological analyses indicated that these specimens belong to a distinct entity which we propose to describe as a new species under the name 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA5FF91FF76F7E1FEFCF7F9" authorityName="G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S. M. Boo" authorityYear="2014" box="[245,335,2049,2076]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="11" pageNumber="212" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="ulixei">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FF76F7E1FEB0F7FE" box="[245,259,2050,2076]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA5FF91FE92F7E2FEFCF7F9" box="[273,335,2049,2075]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">ulixei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B0CB43DEFFA2FF96FF0BFA04FB4EF9C3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5150062" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5150062" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5150062/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" startId="12.[136,229,1511,1533]" targetBox="[363,1229,201,1486]" targetPageId="12">
