<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA2FF96FF0BF9ACFC85F98B" blockId="12.[136,822,1615,1678]" box="[136,822,1615,1642]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
Section 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA2FF96FF60F9ACFEEBF988" bold="true" box="[227,344,1615,1642]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Horridum</emphasis>
G. Andrade-Sorcia &amp; S.M. Boo, 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA2FF96FD4CF9B3FC85F98B" box="[719,822,1616,1641]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">sect. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA2FF96FF0BF990FCA9F96C" blockId="12.[136,822,1615,1678]" box="[136,794,1651,1678]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
Heterotypic synonym: group 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA2FF96FE52F990FD9EF96F" box="[465,557,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Sinicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="80256EA7FFA2FF96FDB7F997FCA9F96C" author="Dawson, E. Y." box="[564,794,1651,1678]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="237 - 250" refId="ref12682" refString="Dawson, E. Y. (1944) The marine algae of the Gulf of California. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions 3: 237 - 250." type="journal article" year="1944">Dawson (1944: 245)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA2FF96FF0BF95CFEDFF86B" blockId="12.[136,1453,1727,1965]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
Thalli with wood-like holdfasts initially discoid and becoming conical or hapteroid. The stipe and branches are cylindrical with spiny (muricate) margins. Leaf-like blades lanceolate, mostly 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA2FF96FD65F900FCE3F91A" box="[742,848,1763,1785]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" unit="mm" value="45.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="30.0">30–60 mm</quantity>
long, and 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA2FF96FC3EF900FBBCF91A" box="[957,1039,1763,1784]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3–8 mm</quantity>
wide. Some blades are undulated, with a prominent nerve serrated margins, and numerous cryptostomata. Vesicles spherical, smooth, or spiny, 3.0– 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA2FF96FB62F8E4FA9EF8FE" box="[1249,1325,1799,1821]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Cryptostomata could be observed on the vesiclesand the thallus. Receptacles cylindrical, with multiple branches, showing spiny or smooth margins, growing from the middle part of the thallus to the apical side. Thalli reached up to 
<quantity id="234CBEB3FFA2FF96FB2EF8ACFB5AF886" box="[1197,1257,1871,1893]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
in length, rigid and densely branched.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACAE40DDFFA2FF97FF0BF874FD18FF5A" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="214" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA2FF96FF0BF874FD51F84F" blockId="12.[136,1453,1727,1965]" box="[136,738,1943,1965]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA2FF96FF0BF874FF69F84E" bold="true" box="[136,218,1943,1964]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<typeStatus id="3B0FADF4FFA2FF96FF0BF874FF0EF84E" box="[136,189,1943,1964]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Type</typeStatus>
:—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA2FF96FF59F874FD6DF84F" authority="Setchell &amp; Gardner (1924: 734)" authorityName="Setchell &amp; Gardner" authorityPageNumber="734" authorityYear="1924" box="[218,734,1943,1965]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA2FF96FF59F874FE17F84E" box="[218,420,1943,1964]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Sargassum horridum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="80256EA7FFA2FF96FE2AF874FD6DF84F" author="Setchell, W. A. &amp; Gardner, N. L." box="[425,734,1943,1965]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" pagination="695 - 949" refId="ref15076" refString="Setchell, W. A. &amp; Gardner, N. L. (1924) The Marine Algae, in Expedition of the California Academy of Sciences to the Gulf of California in 1921. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences Series 4 12 (29): 695 - 949." type="journal article" year="1924">Setchell &amp; Gardner (1924: 734)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA2FF96FF0BF838FD84F7FB" blockId="12.[136,1451,2011,2074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA2FF96FF0BF838FEBAF817" bold="true" box="[136,265,2011,2037]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Habitat:—</emphasis>
Growth was observed on rocks or calcareous substrates (as shells) in the intertidal or subtidal zone, some thalli were growing in intertidal pools.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA3FF97FF3EFF7EFD18FF5A" blockId="13.[136,1452,157,364]" box="[189,683,157,184]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FF3EFF7EFE6AFF55" bold="true" box="[189,473,157,183]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Current distribution:—</emphasis>
Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="2670DDB4FFA3FF97FDB2FF7DFD15FF5A" box="[561,678,158,184]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">California</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACAE40DDFFA3FF97FF3EFF21FEB2FE8E" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E40B1356FFA3FF97FF3EFF21FEB2FE8E" blockId="13.[136,1452,157,364]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FF3EFF21FEFCFF3E" bold="true" box="[189,335,194,220]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Remarks:—</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="80256EA7FFA3FF97FED3FF21FDA0FF3E" author="Dawson, E. Y." box="[336,531,194,220]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" pagination="237 - 250" refId="ref12682" refString="Dawson, E. Y. (1944) The marine algae of the Gulf of California. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions 3: 237 - 250." type="journal article" year="1944">Dawson’s (1944)</bibRefCitation>
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FD9DFF21FDC9FF3E" box="[542,634,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Sinicola</emphasis>
group was described using characters from Setchell 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FB67FF21FB49FF3E" box="[1252,1274,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">&amp;</emphasis>
Gardner’s first description for 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FEBDFF05FD86FEE2" box="[318,565,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA3FF97FEBDFF05FD82FEE2" authorityName="Setchell &amp; Gardner" authorityYear="1924" box="[318,561,230,256]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="horridum">Sargassum horridum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We suggest to rename this group as section 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FBD7FF05FB77FEE2" box="[1108,1220,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Horridum</emphasis>
instead of 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FAD3FF05FA1FFEE2" box="[1360,1452,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Sinicola</emphasis>
considering 
<taxonomicName id="23B468D5FFA3FF97FE95FEE9FDB5FEC6" authorityName="Setchell &amp; Gardner" authorityYear="1924" box="[278,518,266,292]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FE95FEE9FDB5FEC6" box="[278,518,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Sargassum horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characters as the most representative. Note that group 
<emphasis id="D6C0CF44FFA3FF97FB17FEE9FB43FEC6" box="[1172,1264,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Sinicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="80256EA7FFA3FF97FB78FEE9FF08FEAB" author="Dawson, E. Y." pageId="13" pageNumber="214" pagination="237 - 250" refId="ref12682" refString="Dawson, E. Y. (1944) The marine algae of the Gulf of California. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions 3: 237 - 250." type="journal article" year="1944">Dawson (1944: 245)</bibRefCitation>
does not retain nomenclatural priority (ICN art. 37.3). This section is currently distributed along the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion id="2670DDB4FFA3FF97FF0BFEB1FF4EFE8E" box="[136,253,338,364]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">California</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
